<subSubSection pageId="7" pageNumber="563" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1436,1266,1435]" pageId="7" pageNumber="563">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,321,1374,1399]" pageId="7" pageNumber="563">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Closely related to 
<taxonomicName box="[576,839,1374,1398]" class="Insecta" family="Aradidae" genus="Longitergus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="563" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="productus" status="n.sp.">
<emphasis box="[576,839,1374,1398]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="563">Longitergus productus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[856,911,1375,1398]" pageId="7" pageNumber="563" rank="species">n.sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, sharing all essential body structures and dimensions, from which it is distinguished by the characters given below.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1248,1482,1867]" box="[433,1067,1482,1507]" pageId="7" pageNumber="563">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[433,1067,1482,1507]" pageId="7" pageNumber="563">
<taxonomicName box="[433,579,1482,1507]" class="Insecta" family="Aradidae" genus="Longitergus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="563" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="productus" status="n.sp.">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[433,579,1482,1507]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="563">L. productus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[579,635,1482,1507]" pageId="7" pageNumber="563" rank="species">n.sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
<taxonomicName box="[905,1004,1482,1507]" class="Insecta" family="Aradidae" genus="Longitergus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="563" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="similis" status="n.sp.">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[905,1004,1482,1507]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="563">L.similis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1011,1067,1482,1507]" pageId="7" pageNumber="563" rank="species">n.sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1248,1482,1867]" box="[151,1049,1518,1543]" pageId="7" pageNumber="563">Pronotum: (Figs. 1,12,15) (Figs. 18,21)</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1248,1482,1867]" box="[151,1166,1554,1579]" pageId="7" pageNumber="563">Anterolateral angles angulate, margins beset with more rounded, margins</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1248,1482,1867]" box="[433,1219,1590,1615]" pageId="7" pageNumber="563">setigerous tubercles without setigerous tubercles</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1248,1482,1867]" box="[151,1192,1626,1651]" pageId="7" pageNumber="563">Disk medially wide granulate ridge narrower granulate carina</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1248,1482,1867]" pageId="7" pageNumber="563">Posterolateral humeri without granulate elevation distinct granulate elevation posteriorly of sublateral carina posteriorly of sublateral carina</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1248,1482,1867]" box="[151,1224,1734,1759]" pageId="7" pageNumber="563">Pilosity of legs and long, stiff and erect setae on short and adpressed setae on</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1248,1482,1867]" box="[151,1096,1770,1795]" pageId="7" pageNumber="563">Antennae larger tubercles smaller tubercles</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1248,1482,1867]" box="[151,1056,1806,1831]" pageId="7" pageNumber="563">
Genitalic stuctures (
<figureCitation box="[441,561,1806,1831]" captionStart="FIGURES 2 – 11" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1924,1946]" captionTargetBox="[164,1414,180,1845]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,169,1900]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 2 – 11. Longitergus productus n. sp., male paratype. 2 — lateral view, antennae and legs partly removed; 3 — terminal ventral segments VI – VIII; 4 — pygophore dorsal view; 5 — pygophore ventral view; 6 – 8 — right paramere in different positions; 9 – 11 — phallus in dorsal, lateral and ventral position. Scale bar for Figs. 2, 3 = 1.25 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/223616/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="563">
Figs. 
<number box="[505,561,1806,1831]" pageId="7" pageNumber="563" value="8.5" valueMax="11.0" valueMin="6.0">6–11</number>
</figureCitation>
) (
<figureCitation box="[914,1048,1806,1831]" captionStart="FIGURES 24 – 33" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1811,1833]" captionTargetBox="[152,1415,195,1810]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[151,1436,155,1815]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 24 – 33. Longitergus similis n. sp. male genitalic structures. 24 – 26 — pygophore dorsal, lateral and ventral; 27 – 30 — right paramere in different positions; 31 – 33 — phallus in dorsal, lateral and ventral position. Scale bar = 0.2 mm for Figs. 27 – 30." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/223619/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="563">
Figs. 
<number box="[977,1048,1807,1831]" pageId="7" pageNumber="563" value="30.0" valueMax="33.0" valueMin="27.0">27–33</number>
</figureCitation>
)
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1248,1482,1867]" box="[151,336,1842,1867]" pageId="7" pageNumber="563">(see differences)</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1436,1914,2011]" pageId="7" pageNumber="563">
Other smaller differences observed range within the expected variability and are not of specific value. 
<collectingCountry box="[1362,1393,1915,1939]" name="American Samoa" pageId="7" pageNumber="563">As</collectingCountry>
the detailed description of 
<taxonomicName box="[406,547,1950,1974]" class="Insecta" family="Aradidae" genus="Longitergus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="563" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="productus">
<emphasis box="[406,547,1950,1974]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="563">L. productus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
n.sp fits perfectly—except the differences listed above—also to 
<taxonomicName box="[1267,1369,1950,1974]" class="Insecta" family="Aradidae" genus="Longitergus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="563" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="similis" status="n.sp.">
<emphasis box="[1267,1369,1950,1974]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="563">L. similis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1376,1431,1951,1974]" pageId="7" pageNumber="563" rank="species">n.sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, it seems unreasonable to repeat its description. The new species can be easily recognized..
</paragraph>
